article.headline: Winthrop 71, Radford 44
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- Craig Bradshaw scored 19 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to give Winthrop a 71-44 victory over Radford on Saturday. The Eagles (16-6, 10-2 Big South Conference) grabbed an early 10-point lead and went ahead 31-22 at halftime. Bradshaw had 15 points in the opening half. Winthrop started the second half with a 14-6 run and increased its lead to 20 with 9:09 remaining. James Shuler had 12 points in the second half. Whit Holcomb-Faye led the Highlanders (13-11, 6-6) with 16 points. He was the only Radford player in double figures. The Eagles outrebounded Radford 49-33 and outscored the Highlanders 26-4 in the paint.
